cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new type of convolutional layer for deep neural networks and evaluates its performance on image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the optimization difficulties of deep networks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the proposed layer involves aggregation of features, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the experiments involve benchmark datasets, which could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
